node.accessibility_caption: A trail passport sits amongst pine needles at the start of a wooded trail.

node.text:
September 1st marks the return of our local @1percentftp partner @freeportconservationtrust ‘s Freeport Trail Challenge!⁣
⁣
You have from September 1st to October 31st to hike the four designated trails. Get all four stamps on your passport and you will be rewarded. Adults, kids, dogs, everyone is eligible to participate in the challenge and receive some fun prizes for completion as well as be entered in drawings for some great raffle prizes. ⁣
⁣
This is the 7th year of celebrating the beauty that Freeport has to offer, and whether you are joining for the first time or have been with us every step of the way, we welcome you. ⁣
⁣
You can pick up your trail challenge passport at our tasting room, and stay tuned for the announcement of the trail challenge wrap up party!

node.accessibility_caption: A bottle of MO next to a MO sign

node.text:
A staff favorite, MO our American Pale Ale is back! ⁣
⁣
Brewed with Falconer’s Flight and Simcoe this beer is the perfect middle ground between Peeper and Lunch. ⁣
⁣
Available in bottles and on draft in our tasting room and headed out to distribution this week. ⁣

node.accessibility_caption: A brewer stands in front of a brewery centrifuge holding a bottle of Black Barn Program No. 25 Session IPA

node.text:
Today we release Black Barn Program No. 25 Session IPA on draft and in bottles exclusively from our tasting room. ⁣
⁣
This recipe from our brewer Chris, features Citra, Mosaic, and HBC 586 hops, as well as local malts from both @blueoxmalthouse and @mainemalthouse . Using an unconventional hopping method (omitting all boil additions and relying exclusively on a hefty whirlpool charge) to minimize bitterness, and amplify the hop aromatics, this 4.5% Session IPA has upfront aromas of pineapple and mango, followed by notes of lemon, pine and peach. ⁣
⁣
We hope you enjoy this last shout out to summer!

node.accessibility_caption: Morro Bay in CA

node.text:
It's time once again to announce our @1percentftp staff scholarship in which our staff submit applications for a @1percentftp nonprofit that they are passionate about and/or personally involved with. Each month we choose one of these nonprofits to receive a $1000 scholarship from our company. For the month of August our tasting room team member Lily's submission of @morrobaynep was the recipient.⁣
⁣
@morrobaynep in CA works to protect and restore Morro Bay and its watershed by conducting monitoring and research to track the health of the estuary, repairing natural habitats to protect water quality and wildlife, and educating residents and visitors on how to be good stewards of the bay.⁣
⁣
The Estuary Program is one of 28 National Estuary Programs across the country (including the Casco Bay Estuary Partnership here in Maine) that are working to safeguard and improve the health of some of our nation’s most important coastal waters. When Lily visited this area with her family she was struck by how beautiful and clean the coast was, and felt that their work fit in with the environmental goals supported by Maine Beer Company. Programs like this around the country are playing a vital role in helping us understand the importance of clean and healthy waterways, and the actions we can take to fight climate change. ⁣
⁣
Thank you to @morrobaynep for the important work they do, and to Lily for the nomination! (📷 @morrobaynep )

node.text:
Can’t beat a day exploring Maine’s coast!⁣
⁣
We recently made another visit out to Little Whaleboat Island to share why we’re supporting @maine_coast_heritage_trust ‘s efforts to purchase these undeveloped islands and keep them open to the public. ⁣
⁣
Click the link in our bio to learn more and join in the effort!

node.text:
A throwback to our original sign. Back at our first location on Industrial Way in Portland, our cofounder David realized we needed some way for people to find us (not many visitors in those days but certainly our vendors!)⁣
⁣
With a pretty minimal budget he pulled together this sign, and while it’s nothing fancy, it was a great starting point and still hangs in our tasting room today as a reminder of how we got started.

node.text:
Today is the 5th anniversary of the designation of Katahdin Woods & Waters National Monument. This past weekend we celebrated with @friendsofkatahdinwoodswaters the five years that this space has been part of the National Park Service while honoring the over 11,000-year relationship that the Penobscot Indian Nation and other Wabanaki Nations have with this landscape.⁣
⁣
We are excited to see the increased use of the monument over the past 5 years through the development of park infrastructure, new employees, new trails, and community programming for all ages. This brief time as a monument has shown the importance of land preservation for both the environment, and the continued enjoyment and use of these spaces by multiple generations of people.

node.text:
After a little delay to make sure it was tasting perfect, today we release Black Barn Program No. 24 Kölsch Style Ale in bottles and on draft exclusively from our tasting room!⁣
⁣
The inspiration for this Kölsch was mixing traditional German malts and yeast with some US grown malt and hops. The result is a lager-like ale without the fuss of an eight week fermenter residency. (Plus who doesn’t like a good umlaut!)⁣
⁣
Our packaging team member Abby worked with our brewer Paul to perfect the recipe. This beer has initial aromas of lemon, honey and rose, followed by notes of fresh cut grass, sulfur and bread dough. Enjoy!

node.text:
Good morning from Shin Pond Maine. We’re up in the North Woods this weekend to celebrate the 5th anniversary of the designation of Katahdin Woods & Waters National Monument. ⁣
⁣
We’re fueling up before heading out for some hikes today and joining @friendsofkatahdinwoodswaters later for the anniversary party tonight!

node.accessibility_caption: A glass of Fall stout sits on top of red leaves on a barrel.

node.text:
We love the smell of coffee in the morning. Smells like…we’re brewing Fall!⁣
⁣
Yeah, it might crack 90 degrees today, but autumn is coming, so today we brew our seasonal coffee stout, Fall. ⁣
⁣
Made with the addition of cold brew from our friends @coffeebydesign , this 5.6% stout has notes of coffee, chocolate, molasses, cedar, and citrus. ⁣
⁣
We’ll announce the release in a few weeks. Fall will be available in bottles and on draft in our tasting room and then head out to distribution shortly after.
